The second deputy general secretary of the SACP has accused President Zuma of disregarding ANC policies regarding the succession debate. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Communist Party (SACP) s Solly Mapaila has called on the African National Congress (ANC) to rein in President Jacob Zuma, saying the president has been disregarding ANC policies regarding the succession debate.Mapaila who s the party s second deputy general secretary has been addressing supporters at the Moses Kotane Memorial Lecture in Rustenburg in the North West.Last Sunday, President Zuma endorsed Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma telling supporters the former African Union commission chair loves the country and has a good track record.Mapaila says the president must be controlled. If you want to restore credibility in the organisation; the top leadership must set an unequal example so that all the members can aspire to reach that higher example. But what we re now seeing is that there s acceptance to disregard ANC policies. LISTEN: Zuma directly endorses Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma for presidency(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)